title: Boeing preparing to ship milestone O3b mPower satellites for launch
summary: The last pair of satellites SES needs to provide upgraded broadband services from medium Earth orbit have completed tests ahead of an early June launch, SES said during financial results May 4.

title: O3b mPower faces delays as SES investigates electrical issue
summary: SES needs to conduct extra tests before launching its next pair of O3b mPower satellites, the operator said Aug. 3, to investigate a glitch that is sporadically tripping off power modules on its first four in medium Earth orbit.

title: SES Investigation Delays Next O3b mPower Mission
summary: Satellite operator SES has announced that it will conduct extra tests before proceeding with the launch of its next pair of O3b mPower satellites.

title: Launch Roundup: North Korea has failed launch attempt, SpaceX launch back-to-back missions
summary: Following several launch delays last week, the week of Aug. 21 through Aug. 27 is set to see seven launches marking the 129th through 135th orbital launch attempts of 2023.
